[2026-03-18T11:29:26.499Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01REFs1EamLfYFg9f6gJFSQ9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The fix is complete. Here's what was done:\n\n**Problem:** `processQueue()` is async and called from multiple event handlers (`worker-ready`, `worker-connected`, `complete`, `busy`, `submit`). Two concurrent calls could both call `getIdleWorker()` before either called `pool.assign()`, returning the same worker ID. The second `assign()` would fail, and the re-queued item via `unshift` would corrupt FIFO ordering.\n\n**Fix:** Added a `dispatching` boolean guard flag. When `processQueue` is already running, subsequent calls return immediately. The existing `while` loop naturally handles items added to the queue during `await` points — after each `dispatchToWorker` completes, the loop re-checks `queue.length` and `getIdleWorker()`, picking up any new items or newly-idle workers that arrived during the await. The `finally` block ensures the guard is always released, even on early returns.\n\nThis eliminates the race without changing the dispatch semantics or requiring any structural refactoring."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":397,"cache_read_input_tokens":43536,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":397},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"aefd2344-322a-4270-982f-2978aca96abe","uuid":"06455936-ba3f-4560-bb6d-6887f00d2665"}
